FAQ


Q: How long does it take to sell structured settlement annuity payments?
A: Generally it takes 45-60 days to sell structured settlement annuity payments. It depends on the jurisdiction or county where the Payee lives and whether or not the annuity payments are life contingent


Q: Can I sell life contingent structured settlement annuity payments?
A: We are experts at buying life contingent structured settlement annuity payments. Although we can't guarantee the Payee will qualify for life insurance we know exactly how to proceed with each case.


Q: Will I receive a check or a bank wire if I decide to sell my structured settlement annuity?
A: We prefer to wire your funding check directly into your bank account. We'll ask that you fill out a Funding Instructions form that you'll have notarized. We cannot send closing funds to a third party.


Q: Do I have to go to a court hearing in order to sell structured settlement annuity payments?
A: Generally yes, however there are several states that don't require your physical appearance. In those states your Affidavit is used to help the judge decide. Hearings normally only last a few minutes.


Q: What are the chances my request to sell structured settlement payments gets approved?
A: The majority of structured settlement transfers are approved. The petition to transfer payment rights must be in your best interest. Occasionally transfer requests are denied due to poor reasoning.


Q: How can I get a quote for structured settlement annuity payments?
A: Simply fill out the quote request form in the upper right corner of our site or pick up the phone and call us to get a quote for structured settlement annuity payments. Call +1 (888) 852-5658.


Q: Can I sell just a portion of my structured settlement annuity or do I have to sell the whole thing?
A: If your annuity payments are large enough, then yes, you can sell just a portion of your structured settlement annuity. If they are very small then it may not be possible due to legal costs involved.


Q: What documents do you need from me if I want to sell structured settlement annuity payments?
A: Generally we'll need a copy of your Annuity Contract, Divorce Decree (if divorced), Driver's License or State ID, Release & Settlement Agreement (We can help you get it) and your Social Security Card.






















